import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='source', bins=30, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['source'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['source'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of source nodes in the flare visualization?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='source', y='target')
    plt.title("What is the relationship between source and target nodes in the flare visualization?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Source")
    plt.ylabel("Target")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    source_counts = data['source'].value_counts().head(10)
    top_sources = source_counts.index
    top_counts = source_counts.values

    sns.barplot(x=top_sources, y=top_counts, palette="viridis")
    plt.xlabel("Source Node")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.title("What is the most common source node in the flare visualization?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend(top_sources, title="Source Nodes", loc="upper right")

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    target_counts = data['target'].value_counts().head(10)
    top_targets = target_counts.index.tolist()
    top_target_counts = target_counts.values.tolist()

    sns.barplot(x=top_targets, y=top_target_counts, palette='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Target Nodes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the most common target node in the flare visualization?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend([f'Top 10 Target Nodes'], loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
